OL,6,FThe Premier League reviews clubs'
OL,7,Faccounts every year and sets a limit
OL,8,Fon the extent to which they can keep
OL,9,Frunning at a loss. In summary, clubs
OL,10,Fmust not lose more than #105m over a
OL,11,Fthree-year period.
OL,13,FIn terms of revenue, only a club's
OL,14,Foutgoings in transfers, employee
OL,15,Fbenefits (including wages), finance
OL,16,Fcosts and dividends will be considered
OL,17,Fover income from match-day sales, TV
OL,18,Frevenue, advertising, finance, player
OL,19,Fsales and prize money.
